5.2 Exemptions. The confidentiality and non-use obligations imposed upon the Receiving Party under paragraph 5.1 shall only be binding if the Receiving Party fails to demonstrate, beyond a reasonable doubt, that the disclosure of the information is necessary for one or more of the following reasons:

a) Compliance with any applicable law, rule, regulation, or legal process;
b) Protection of the Receiving Party's legitimate interests;
c) The public interest or common good.

In all other cases, the Receiving Party shall maintain the confidentiality and non-use of such information as required by paragraph 5.1.
